genresAdvancedInfo.name: afro-cuban percussion
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This genre is characterized by the use of traditional Cuban percussion instruments such as congas, bongos, and timbales to create complex rhythms and polyrhythms. It blends African and Cuban influences to create an energetic and rhythmic sound that is used in both traditional and contemporary music.
